This press briefing by Press Secretary Jay Carney covers a range of topics. Carney provides an update on the federal government's response to events affecting areas across the country, such as Hurricane Irene and the major fires in Texas. He also discusses the President's upcoming speech to Congress, where he will propose a jobs and growth package. Carney emphasizes the need for bipartisan cooperation and action to address the economy and create jobs. He mentions specific proposals that have enjoyed bipartisan support in the past, such as extending the payroll tax cut and establishing an infrastructure bank. Carney also addresses questions about the European crisis, the President's approval ratings, and the Palestinian Authority's plan to seek recognition at the UN. He concludes by saying that the President's proposals will be paid for and will include measures to address the deficit and debt.